## Testing plan

Gates that apply: `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `build`: solution builds with the extended `BeamTree.fs`, the two new UI files (against the FuncUI DSL surface, NO clone dependency, §0 constraint 5), and the filled serialization/schema.
- `unit-tests`: existing `BerremanTests` stays green (`count_at_least` baseline from the prior slice's state-of-the-world).
- `constructor-unit-tests`: `BeamTreeTests.fs` (mirror rejects `Transmitted`, accepts `Reflected`; non-mirror holds both; linear chain single-child — AC-B2/AC-B3); `BeamRoutingTests.fs` (child incident field = parent branch field via `EmField.propagate`; root solve via `OpticalSystemSolver`/`Solution.emSys`; independent detector branches — AC-A3/AC-B1/AC-B4); `StackEditTests.fs` (add/delete/reorder/duplicate/group, substrate switch, medium selectors, `discretize` — AC-B5/B6/B7/B11); `ProjectJsonRoundtripTests.fs` (beam-tree JSON round-trip, default-unit hook preserved, no `.binz`, SI unchanged — AC-A2/A5/B8/B9/D6).
- Emit the state-of-the-world file with the `gates:` YAML baseline block.

## Risks

- **Medium:** beam-tree solver-driving and `EmField.propagate` routing (B.1/B.4) must use the engine's `BaseOpticalSystemSolver(emf, system)` overload (`Solvers.fs:149`) and `ShortOpticalSystem` exactly; a mismatched feed form fails the routing test. Verify the overload signature against `Solvers.fs` before wiring.
- **Medium:** the UI files (`StackEditor.fs`, `ConstructionPage.fs`) must compile against the FuncUI DSL surface WITHOUT adding the clone dependency (§0 constraint 5; A.6/A.9). Keep them buildable skeletons whose `update` contains no Avalonia type (P3 testability).
- **Low:** the `beamNode`/`beamBranch` `$defs` must stay anchored exactly as Part A reserved them; renaming an anchor breaks Part I validation.

## Hand-off

State carried to later slices:
- `BeamTree.fs` now drives the reused solver per node, routes branches via `EmField.propagate`, enforces the mirror reflected-only rule, carries the default-unit hook, and discretizes gradient layers. Slice 004 (Part C) extends `ConstructorElement` handling with the curved-element zone fan; slice 010 (Part J §J.12) renders the solved tree.
- The `beamNode`/`beamBranch`/`opticalSystem`/`layer`/`unitOfMeasure` `$defs` are filled at field level; Part I (slice 009) wires validate-on-load and round-trip identity over them.
- `StackEditor.fs` and `ConstructionPage.fs` exist as the construction surface; slice 010 (Part J) adds the schematic view, drag-and-drop onto layer rows (J.4), repeat builder (J.2), and the shared shell that hosts this page.
- The per-element default-unit hook is in place on `BeamNode`/layer rows; Part E (slice 005) places the corresponding hook on `SourceSpec`.

Per `arc-runner.system-md`, emit the state-of-the-world file with a fenced YAML `gates:` block:

```yaml
gates:
  berreman_unit_tests: <int>
```
